External rules in Inventor allow you to trigger custom iLogic scripts based on vault lifecycle events (save, check-in, release, etc.).

Step-by-Step Setup:
1. Prepare Your iLogic Script
Your ExportPDFOnVault.ivb script is ready to use. Make sure it's in your Inventor project folder or user library.

2. Configure the Vault Lifecycle State (if needed)
In Autodesk Vault:

Go to Administration > Vault Settings > Lifecycle States
Define the state(s) where you want the PDF export to trigger (usually on "Released" or "Submitted for Review")
3. Add the External Rule via Vault Admin
In Autodesk Vault Admin Console:

Navigate to Automation > External Rules
Click New External Rule
Configure:
Name: "Export PDF on Save"
Script: Browse to your ExportPDFOnVault.ivb
Trigger Event: Select from:
File Save
State Change
Check-In
Release
Entity Types: Drawing (*.idw)
Condition (optional): Filter by file type, state, etc.
4. Set Permissions
Run As: Service account with proper vault rights
Error Handling: Choose to fail silently or log errors
5. Test the Rule
Open a drawing in Inventor
Save it to vault
Monitor the vault logs for execution results
Verify the PDF was created in the configured directory
Troubleshooting Tips:
Issue	Solution
Script not executing	Check vault logs at C:\Program Files\Autodesk\Vault Server\Logs\
Permission denied on PDF export	Run vault service with elevated privileges
PDF path not found	Use absolute path or relative to vault workspace
No PDF created	Verify script syntax and Inventor version compatibility
Alternative: Direct Rule in Inventor
If you want the rule to run every time you save locally (not just in vault):

In Inventor: Tools > iLogic > Edit Module
Paste your script
Add an event trigger via Tools > iLogic > External Rules
